<F P=100> HONG KONG &amp; MACAO </F>
<F P=101> Hong Kong </F>
<H3> <TI>   XINHUA Chief Comments on Upcoming NPC Session </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK0803080694 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE in Chinese 1352 GMT 
7 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK0803080694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporters Gan Zhebin (3927 0772 2430) and Zhang Lei </F>
(1728 7191)] 
  [Text] Beijing, 7 Mar (ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE)--Upon his 
arrival in Beijing from Hong Kong today to attend the Second 
Session of the Eighth National People's Congress [NPC], Zhou 
Nan, NPC deputy and director of the Hong Kong Branch of the 
XINHUA NEWS AGENCY, told reporters during a special interview 
that, although the British side is not cooperating on the Hong 
Kong issue, the Chinese side, along with the Hong Kong 
compatriots, can absolutely ensure Hong Kong's steady transition 
and prolonged prosperity and stability. This is beyond 
question, and no force can stop us from achieving this objective. 
  Zhou Nan said: We are now in an important period for the 
country to carry out reform and opening up and establish the 
socialist market economy. Some major reform measures will be 
introduced. We hope to solicit opinions through these "two 
sessions" and correctly handle the relations between 
development, stability, and reform. In addition, we will 
further carry out the policy of "doing two types of work 
simultaneously," namely, we will pay attention to material and 
spiritual civilizations and to the formation of the democratic 
and legal systems to enable the country's economic modernization 
to embark on a healthy track. 
  One of the two reporters asked if the Hong Kong issue would 
become a hot topic at the "two sessions." Zhou Nan said he 
believed that Premier Li Peng's government work report would 
refer to the Hong Kong issue, that the Hong Kong NPC deputies 
and members as well as the mainland NPC deputies and members 
will make some comments on the Hong Kong situation, and that, to 
express state and popular intentions, the NPC and the National 
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative 
Conference will, of course, respond to this issue. 

</TEXT>

