<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reportage on CPPCC Second Plenary Session </TI></H3>
<H4>   Role in State Affairs Detailed </H4>
<F P=102> OW0803075994 Beijing XINHUA in English 0742 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0803075994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 8 (XINHUA) -- The Chinese People's 
Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) has played an 
important role in China's political, economic and cultural 
affairs, Ye Xuanping, vice-chairman of the Eighth National 
Committee of CPPCC, said here today. 
  Ye said that the CPPCC Eighth National Committee, based on 
the work experience of the previous national committees, has 
probed new ways to engage in political consultations and 
exercise democratic supervision. It has tried to make CPPCC, a 
unique form of democratic politics in China, meet the 
requirements of the country's socialist modernization since its 
first session last March, he said. 
  Ye made the remarks when delivering the work report of the 
Standing Committee of the CPPCC Eighth National Committee at the 
opening of its second session. 
  In the past year, Ye said, the National Committee held five 
standing committee meetings and discussed a wide range of issues 
including the national economic situation, measures to solve 
economic problems, the international situation, establishment of 
a socialist market economy in China, measures to ensure a clean 
government and the fight against corruption. 
  Zhu Rongji and other leaders of the Communist Party of China 
(CPC) delivered reports to the Standing Committee. 
  The Standing Committee of the CPPCC National Committee put 
forward many good opinions and suggestions on the issues, 
according to Ye. For instance, the economic sub-committee of 
the National Committee raised suggestions on strengthening 
macro-economic controls and keeping inflation at bay, which were 
adopted by the CPC Central Committee and the central government. 
The sub-committee has therefore contributed to strengthened 
macroeconomic controls and a continuous, fast and healthy 
development of the national economy. 
  Last year, Li Ruihuan, chairman of the CPPCC National 
Committee, successfully visited Nepal, India and Pakistan. It 
was the first visit to foreign countries by a chairman of the 
CPPCC National Committee and has important significance in 
CPPCC's international exchanges. 
  The national committee organized 15 delegations for visits 
to 
more than 20 countries and established ties with organizations 
and parliaments of 14 host countries. So far, the CPPCC 
National Committee has established friendly relations with 46 
organizations and parliaments in 36 countries. 
  Subcommittees of the CPPCC National Committee also made 
surveys on some important issues and put forward 24 reports. 
They attracted attention from the CPC Central Committee, the 
State Council, government departments and local authorities. 
Many suggestions contained in the reports have been adopted. 
  In addition, the national committee has also made new 
progress in expanding domestic and overseas friendship ties, 
promoting the reunification of the motherland, participating in 
the anti- corruption campaign, helping state organs build clean 
government, improving inspection work of its members, raising 
suggestions for reform and development, improving the handling 
of proposals raised by CPPCC members, and revising the 
constitution of CPPCC. 
  On this year's work, Ye Xuanping said that the CPPCC 
National 
Committee will uphold the banner of patriotism and socialism, 
focus on the central work of CPC and the state, actively engage 
in political consultations and exercise democratic supervision, 
improve its work efficiency, seize favorable development 
opportunities, and make further contributions to the country's 
economic reform, open policy implementation, economic 
development and social stability. 
  Ye said, the CPPCC National Committee in the New Year will 
make systematic and in-depth investigations on issues concerning 
economic development, reform, the open policy and people's life, 
put forward policy proposals and report them to the CPC Central 
Committee and the State Council. CPPCC, Ye said, will make 
better use of itself as a pool of talented people, its extensive 
information sources and its wide contacts. 
  In the New Year, Ye said, the CPPCC National Committee will 
continue to develop friendly exchanges with parliaments and 
non-governmental organizations of foreign countries, promote the 
reunification of the motherland, urge direct and two-way 
exchanges of mail, air and shipping services as well as trade 
between the mainland and Taiwan, devote itself to maintaining 
the stability and long-term prosperity of Hong Kong, and work 
for a smooth hand-over and transition of the sovereignty of 
Macao in accordance with the basic law of the territory. 

</TEXT>

