<H3> <TI>   Reportage on CPPCC Second Plenary Session </TI></H3>
<H4>   Tibet Deputies Arrive in Beijing </H4>
<F P=102> OW0703204594 Lhasa Tibet People's Radio Network in Mandarin 
1430 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW0703204594 </F>
<F P=104>  Lhasa Tibet People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "News" program] </F>
  [Excerpts] Tibet's deputies to the Second Session of the 
Eighth National People's Congress [NPC] and members of the 
Second Session of the Eighth Chinese People's Political 
Consultative Conference [CPPCC] National Committee arrived in 
Beijing on the afternoon of 7 March. At Beijing's Xijiao 
Airport, Gyaincain Norbu, NPC deputy and chairman of the Tibet 
Autonomous Regional People's Government, told reporters: We 
feel very honored to represent the over 2 million people of 
various nationalities in Tibet in attending the Second Session 
of the Eighth NPC. We also feel the heavy responsibility. 
Under the current good situation of deepening reform, 
accelerating development, and maintaining stability, I feel 
cheerful at attending the session. [passage omitted] 
  Chen Kuiyuan, NPC deputy and secretary of the Tibet 
Autonomous Regional CPC Committee; Raidi, executive deputy 
secretary of the Tibet Autonomous Regional CPC Committee; 
Sengqen Lozong Gyaincain, vice chairman of Tibet Autonomous 
Regional People's Congress, who were among the first group to 
arrive in Beijing, greeted these deputies and members at the 
guesthouse. 

</TEXT>

