<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hu Jintao Stresses Deepening Reform of Party Schools </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0403154094 Beijing XINHUA in English 1459 GMT 4 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0403154094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 4 (XINHUA) -- Hu Jintao, member of 
the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Central 
Committee of the Chinese Communist Party (CPC), today stressed 
the need to deepen the reform of party school education so as to 
raise it to a new height. 
  At a national working conference of party schools, Hu noted 
that in this vital period in historical development, the 
ideological construction of the party should be put high on the 
agenda. 
  Hu, president of the party school of the CPC Central 
Committee, said that the party schools of all levels are 
responsible for cultivating party officials. 
  He said that it is the basic task of the party to use Deng 
Xiaoping's theory of building socialism with Chinese 
characteristics for theoretic study, publicity work and training 
of party officials. 
  He called for improving the quality of the education, 
enhancing scientific research in the theoretic field, grasping 
the need for the party's education of cadres in this new period, 
and gradually setting up and improving the system of party 
school education in China. 

</TEXT>

