<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Public Security Solve 1.21 Million Criminal Cases in 1993 </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK0803072894 Beijing RENMIN RIBAO in Chinese 3 Mar 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> HK0803072894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing RENMIN RIBAO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Gong Xinwen (7895 6580 2429): "Public Security Organs </F>
Cracked 1.21 Million Criminal Cases Last Year"] 
  [Text] The media spokesman for the Ministry of Public 
Security disclosed that in 1993, public security organs across 
the country received 1.617 million reports of various kinds of 
criminal cases, a 2.2-percent increase over 1992, and that the 
rising tendency of criminal cases has been kept under control. 
Last year, public security organs cracked a total of 1.21 
million criminal cases which occurred in the current year, a 
12.3-percent increase over 1992, and cracked some 290,000 cases 
which occurred in the previous year. Their ability to crack 
criminal cases has obviously improved and efforts against 
criminal activities have been stepped up. 
  Of the 1.617 million criminal reports received by public 
security organs across the country in 1993, 539,000 were very 
serious cases, an 18-percent increase over 1992. 
  At present, public security problems in a few cities and 
counties are comparatively salient and the masses there have 
reacted strongly to this. The Ministry of Public Security has 
already urged public security organs in all localities to step 
up blows and to mainly straighten out order in a few areas where 
public security problems are salient. 

</TEXT>

