<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Third Nuclear Plant To Be Built in Jiujiang, Jiangxi </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK0403140894 Hong Kong ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE in Chinese 0930 
GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK0403140894 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, 3 Mar (ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE)--This 
reporter has learned from relevant quarters that China has 
chosen the Maoziding hill, Pengze county, Jiujiang city of 
Jiangxi as the site for its third nuclear plant. 
  It is learned that the nuclear plant will house six 600,000- 
kilowatt nuclear power units, and that upon completion, it will 
become a key point for electric networks in central and eastern 
China. 
  At present, the Ministry of Power Industry has officially 
confirmed and approved this nuclear power project and 
preliminary stage preparatory work is already underway. Upon 
completion, the nuclear plant will be able to thoroughly resolve 
the electricity shortage of Jiangxi province. 
  At present, China already has the Qinshan Nuclear Plant in 
Zhejiang and the Daya Bay Nuclear Plant in Guangdong. 
Jiujiang's Nuclear Plant will have the largest 
electricity-generating capability, however. 

</TEXT>

