<F P=100> Military </F>
<H3> <TI>   Attends Army Provisions Conference </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0503145694 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1406 
GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW0503145694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By RENMIN RIBAO reporter Mei Hongru (2734 3163 1172) and </F>
XINHUA reporter Jiang Jun (1203 6511)] 
  [Text] Beijing, 2 Mar (XINHUA) -- The People's Liberation 
Army [PLA] General Logistics Department, the Finance Ministry, 
the Ministry of Internal Trade, and the State Grain Reserve 
Bureau jointly convened the Eighth National Army Provisions Work 
Conference today to study reform of the Army provisions supply 
system. 
  Li Lanqing, member of the CPC Central Committee Political 
Bureau and vice premier of the State Council; and Fu Quanyou, 
member of the Central Military Commission [CMC] and director of 
the General Logistics Department; met with representatives to 
the conference. Li Lanqing said: The party Central Committee, 
the State Council, and the CMC have shown concern for and 
attached great importance to the supply of Army provisions, 
which is an important basic task guaranteeing the Army's 
modernization and regularization. Jiang Zemin, CPC Central 
Committee general secretary and CMC chairman, has made important 
instructions on Army provisions work many times. All localities 
and departments have long conscientiously implemented the 
instructions of the party Central Committee and the State 
Council. They have coordinated with one another in doing 
everything possible to ensure the supply, to improve the 
quality, to adjust the variety, and to increase financial 
subsidies for Army provisions, thereby raising the standard of 
Army provisions supply and winning the appreciation of PLA and 
Armed Police officers and men. 
  Li Lanqing emphasized: Army provisions supply is a serious 
political task. Ensuring the supply of Army provisions is of 
great significance to stabilizing and developing Army building 
and guaranteeing national security. Governments at all levels 
and all departments concerned should, as always, do a good job 
in ensuring the variety, quality, quantity, and timeliness of 
Army provisions supply. 
  In his speech, Bai Meiqing, vice minister of internal trade 
and director of the State Grain Reserve Bureau, emphasized the 
necessity of reforming the Army provisions supply system. He 
said: Reform of the Army provisions supply system will begin in 
April this year. Specific points of the reform are as follows: 
The existing method of procuring grains at the state fixed 
price shall be replaced by procurement at negotiated prices and 
supply to Army units at the fixed price. Subsidies for price 
differentials in grains, edible oil, and soybeans supplied to 
the Army shall be shared by both central and provincial-level 
financial resources. Financial affairs related to Army 
provisions shall be managed under special projects, special 
accounts, and special bookkeeping; and funds related to Army 
provisions shall be delivered collectively to the 
provincial-level finance departments for management. After the 
introduction of the reform, state-owned grain enterprises shall 
continue to be responsible for Army provisions supply. Grain 
departments shall be the functioning departments of Army 
provisions supply; and, Army grain supply stations (stores or 
depots) set up by grain departments in various localities shall 
be the special outlets of Army provisions supply. Grain 
departments shall be responsible for arranging and ensuring the 
supply of grains, edible oil, and other provisions for the Army. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-2331 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drchi045_m_94003" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-CHI-94-045 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  8 Mar 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Military </F>
<H3> <TI>   Army Allowed To Transfer Land-Use Rights </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK0403141194 Beijing JIEFANGJUN BAO in Chinese 17 Feb 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> HK0403141194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing JIEFANGJUN BAO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Han Guangqin (7281 1639 2953): "According to </F>
Decision of Ministry of Finance, State Land Administration, and 
PLA General Logistics Department, Army Will Transfer Land Use 
Rights According to Law"] 
  [Text] The Ministry of Finance, the State Land 
Administration, and the PLA General Logistics Department 
recently issued a joint "Circular on Issues Concerning Transfer 
of Surplus Military Land-Use Rights by the Army With 
Compensation." According to the circular, surplus military land 
must be developed in a planned way and under organized 
leadership. The army units which transfer their surplus 
military land must, as required by the relevant state 
regulations, register with the local land administration 
department at the county level and above for the change in the 
land-use right, so that they will be exempted from paying 
charges for transferring land. The proceeds from transferring 
and leasing surplus military land are collected by the General 
Logistics Department and then put into a special account and 
only used as designated. The "Circular" also provides that the 
state will not require the land users to donate to the budget 
adjustment fund and the fund for key construction projects 
including energy and transportation. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-2332 </DOCNO>
