<H3> <TI>   Anhui Helps `Non-Communist' Persons in Development </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0603013294 Beijing XINHUA in English 0108 GMT 6 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0603013294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hefei, March 6 (XINHUA) -- Anhui Province in east 
China has strengthened cooperation with non-Communist Party 
members and non-party personages in social and economic 
development. 
  A survey shows that 158 such people hold leading posts in 
local governments, and a large number of them are serving as 
heads of industrial enterprises, colleges and towns. 
  Encouraged by the provincial government, they have helped 
the 
province to improve work in industry, agriculture, commerce, 
education, science and technology. They have also helped import 
more than 500 projects, involving over 600 million yuan. 
  With their initiative, the province has set up 14 colleges 
and technical schools, a large number of training courses and 
rural industrial enterprises. 

