<H3> <TI>   Zhejiang Builds `Largest' Pumping Station </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0503114194 Beijing XINHUA in English 1050 GMT 5 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0503114194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hangzhou, March 5 (XINHUA) -- Construction of the 
Tianhuanping pumping station, China's largest in Zhejiang 
Province, is in progress. 
  Located in Anji county, the project, which will pump and 
store water at night in order to generate electricity during the 
day time, has been listed as one of China's key capital 
construction projects scheduled for completion next century. 
  With a combined investment of at least 2.3 billion yuan, the 
pumping station will have a total installation capacity of 1.8 
million kilowatts. 
  Its first generating unit is expected to go into operation 
in 
1997. 
  The whole project is being built jointly by the State Energy 
Investment Corporation, Shanghai and Jiangsu, Zhejiang and Anhui 
Provinces. 

</TEXT>

