<F P=100> Northwest Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shaanxi Meeting Outlines Foreign Trade Goals </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK2402030394 Xian Shaanxi People's Radio Network in Mandarin 
0500 GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK2402030394 </F>
<F P=104>  Xian Shaanxi People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At a just-concluded provincial meeting on foreign 
economic and trade relations, Vice Governor Wang Shuangxi asked 
all foreign economic and trade departments in the province to 
speed up reform; transform their operational mechanism; 
establish a new system; and promote the sustained, speedy, and 
healthy [chi xu, kuai su, jian kang] development of the 
province's foreign economic and trade relations. 
  In his speech, Wang Shuangxi confirmed the province's 
achievements in foreign economic and trade relations over the 
last few years. On foreign economic and trade structural 
reform, Wang Shuangxi stressed: First, we should seize the 
opportunity to promote the province's foreign economic and trade 
relations to a new height. Second, we should rationalize 
relations, delegate powers to the lower levels, and exercise 
graded management. Third, we should speed up foreign economic 
and trade structural reform in cities and prefectures; city and 
prefectural foreign trade organizations should be put under city 
and prefectural management and their revenues should be 
separated from the provincial-level foreign trade revenue. 
Fourth, great efforts should be made to transform the foreign 
trade operational mechanism and gradually to form a modern 
enterprise system. 
  Wang Shuangxi also set demands for strengthening leadership 
and transforming functions, saying: The foreign trade tasks set 
by the provincial government are to ensure $1.05 billion in 
foreign exchange earnings through exports this year and to 
strive for $1.1 billion; to increase the number of three-capital 
enterprises to 2,000 by the end of this year; to top $400 
million in foreign capital actually used; to ensure $96 million 
in three-capital enterprises' foreign exchange earnings 
throughout exports; to ensure $40 million in the amount of 
contracts for overseas projects and labor services; to obtain 
three or four international aid projects; and to ensure $20 
million in the amount of contracts for technology exports. 
  Governor Bai Qingcai and Vice Governor Xu Shanlin also 
attended and addressed the meeting. The director of the 
provincial foreign economic relations and trade department made 
a work report at the meeting. Governor Bai Qingcai; Vice 
Governor Wang Shuangxi; Ren Guoyi, vice chairman of the 
provincial people's congress standing committee; and Liang Qi, 
vice chairman of the provincial committee of the Chinese 
People's Political Consultative Conference; attended the closing 
ceremony on 21 February and presented prizes to units that had 
won the glorious title of best enterprise in creating foreign 
exchange earnings in 1993. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

