<F P=100> Central Eurasia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aliyev Meets Entrepreneurs </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0903061694 Beijing XINHUA in English 0601 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0903061694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 9 (XINHUA) -- Visiting Azerbaijani 
President Gaydar Aliyev said here today that his country desires 
to establish direct economic and trade ties with large-sized 
Chinese enterprises. 
  He made the remark at a meeting with the leaders from more 
than 20 large Chinese companies here this morning. 
  The president said that during his visit to China he had 
exchanged views with Chinese leaders on a wide range of issues. 
The two countries also signed a series of important documents 
aimed at promoting the growth of bilateral ties, economic 
co-operation and trade in particular, he said. 
  Aliyev said these agreements should be fully implemented 
through concerted efforts by the relevant departments of the two 
countries. 
  He said China is a big country while Azerbaijan is a young 
country, and both of them have great potential for economic 
development. 
  Azerbaijan, situated at the junction of the continents of 
Europe and Asia, has enjoyed traditional contacts and ties with 
the Asian countries including China. So it can play the role of 
a "bridge" in linking these two continents. 
  Viewed from Azerbaijan's geographical position, there exist 
good conditions for furthering bilateral economic co-operation 
and trade. 
  in his speech, Aliyev also briefed the Chinese entrepreneurs 
on his country's advantages in industry and agriculture, which, 
he said, will lay a basis for bilateral economic co-operation 
and trade. 
  Zheng Hongye, president of the China Council for the 
Promotion of International Trade, noted that a good beginning 
has been made for the pursuit of China-Azerbaijan economic ties 
and trade. 
  He expressed the hope that the entrepreneurs of the two 
countries would frequently exchange visits and deepen their 
mutual understanding so as to further promote such a 
relationship. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

