<H3> <TI>   Guangdong To Set Up `Military Recreation' Zone </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK0503064494 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE in English 1342 GMT 
4 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK0503064494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Guangzhou, March 4 (CNS)--According to relevant 
departments under the Guangdong provincial government, the 
province will set up a military recreation development zone in 
which a number of military entertainment items including a 
shooting range, a site for heavy weapon manoeuvres and a 
sky-diving club will be built. 
  The General staff headquarters of the People's Liberation 
Army (PLA) and Gaoyiao City in Guangdong Province will join in 
the construction of this development zone which has been 
designed to be located on the banks of the Xijiang River, south 
of the city with a total area of two square kilometres. It will 
be divided into four functional sub-divisions with the military 
tourism zone occupying 174,000 square metres and facilities 
including an indoor shooting range, horse-racing track, a site 
for heavy weapon manoeuvres, a site for combat exhibition and a 
sky-diving club. 
  The other three sub-divisions will be a central district 
with 
a total area of 82,000 square metres with an administration 
centre, restaurants, commercial and office buildings, a 
residential area able to house 15,000 households totalling 
53,000 residents and a villa district with a total area of 
41,000 square metres. 
  With the completion of the development zone, the province 
will offer another enjoyable place for entertainment, 
sight-seeing and holidaying for both domestic and foreign 
visitors. 

</TEXT>

