<H3> <TI>   Strike Ends After Intervention by Taxi Company </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK0603033994 Hong Kong LIEN HO PAO in Chinese 5 Mar 94 p 10 </F>
<F P=103> HK0603033994 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong LIEN HO PAO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By staff reporter in Shenzhen: "Taxi Drivers' Strike Ends </F>
After Taxi Company Gives Warning That Those Continuing To Strike 
Will Not Be Allowed To Hire Taxis"] 
  [Text] Following the participation of nearly half of all 
taxi drivers the day before yesterday, the three-day strike 
initiated by Shenzhen taxi drivers basically ended yesterday. 
  A taxi driver estimated that only about 10 percent of the 
drivers continued with the strike yesterday. In front of the 
communications building, taxis again formed a long line to wait 
for passengers. 
  The driver said: The strike ended quickly as a result of the 
involvement of the taxi company. The company issued a circular 
to taxi drivers, saying that if they continued to strike, they 
would not be allowed to hire taxis. The drivers had no 
alternative but to return to work. 
  But some drivers who were still on strike said that they 
would take further action after collecting views from people in 
the same trade. 

</TEXT>

