<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shenzhen Adopts New Entry-Exit System </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0403075294 Beijing XINHUA in English 0653 GMT 4 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0403075294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Shenzhen, March 4 (XINHUA) -- Crossing points in 
this special economic zone bordering Hong Kong have adopted new 
management methods to make it more convenient for people and 
goods to enter and leave. 
  To make the work more efficient, some of the examination and 
management fees are now collected at one go by the city 
immigration office without change of payment standards, instead 
of payment item by item. 
  Beginning May 1 this year, freight vehicles going through 
land ports will receive unified examination concerning customs 
affairs, sanitation and animal and plant quarantine. 
  As a result, freight vehicles entering or leaving the border 
only have to stop twice instead of four times as at present. 
  By the end of the year computers will be installed at the 
crossing points to handle examination and payment. 

</TEXT>

