<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Overseas Businessmen Urged To Invest in Hunan Agriculture </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0403031194 Beijing XINHUA in English 0214 GMT 4 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0403031194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Changsha, March 4 (XINHUA) -- Hunan Province, 
central China, has formulated a series of preferential policies 
to encourage overseas businessmen to invest in local agriculture. 
  The policies involve projects of agricultural infrastructure 
construction, fine-breed livestock production, forestry and 
aquatic production, modern agricultural technology and 
export-oriented agricultural production. 
  According [to] the policies, the investment and co-operation 
can be in the form of funds, materials, industrial property 
rights or special technology. 
  The policies stipulate that overseas businessmen engaged in 
agricultural development and running enterprises in farming, 
animal husbandry and aquatic production can be exempted from 
land rent for 10 to 15 years. 
  Those who run joint ventures in forestry enterprises will be 
exempted from land rent for 20 to 30 years. 
  The provincial government has also drawn up preferential 
policies for export-oriented agricultural production, including 
issuing export licences, and providing pesticides, fertilizer, 
seeds and necessary services. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

