<H3> <TI>   Guizhou Secretary Discusses Helping Impoverished Areas </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK0803131294 Guiyang Guizhou People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 27 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK0803131294 </F>
<F P=104>  Guiyang Guizhou People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At a report meeting held yesterday [27 February] by 
the provincial party committee on inspecting the work to support 
the impoverished in the Mashan and Yaoshan areas, provincial 
party Secretary Liu Fangren stressed: It is necessary to take 
the three actions of racking brains, cherishing deep affection, 
and setting to work in earnest to solve the problem of escaping 
poverty and becoming rich in the Mashan and Yaoshan areas. At 
the report meeting, a videotape on the situation in Mashan and 
Yaoshan was shown. 
  Responsible comrades of the provincial committee of the 
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference and the 
provincial nationality affairs commission made a report on the 
history of and the practical conditions in the Mashan and 
Yaoshan areas, and submitted proposals on changing the 
conditions of these two areas. 
  In his speech, Liu Fangren stressed: Helping the Yaoshan and 
Mashan areas escape poverty and become rich is of great 
significance. It is an issue of strategic and overall 
importance. It is necessary to adopt a special policy and 
measures, and to concentrate our efforts on helping the Yaoshan 
and Mashan areas escape poverty and become rich as early as 
possible. 
  Those who attended the meeting included: provincial party 
and government leaders Chen Shineng, Long Zhiyi, Wang Siqi, Wang 
Guangxian, (Wang Suting), Hu Yunsheng, Huang Yao, Liu Yulin, (Wu 
Xueyong), Yao Jiyuan, Wang Siming, (Dong Sufen), Zhang Chaolun, 
Qiu Yaogao, An Diwei, (Li Yandong), (Wang Demao), (Wu Ruoqiu), 
Jiang Qiwen, (Mao Yupu), and Cheng Tianfu; the responsible 
persons of the relevant provincial departments, of the Qiannan 
and Qianxinan autonomous prefectures, and of Anshun prefecture, 
as well as of Huishui, Changshun, Wangmo, Ziyun, Pintang, and 
Libo counties; and others. 

