<H3> <TI>   Reportage on Eighth National People's Congress Meeting </TI></H3>
<H4>   First Meeting of NPC Presidium </H4>
<F P=102> OW0903053694 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0445 
GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW0903053694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, 9 Mar (XINHUA) -- The Presidium of the 
Second Session of the Eighth National People's Congress [NPC] 
held its first meeting in the Great Hall of the People this 
morning. 
  Chairman Qiao Shi presided over the meeting. The 137 
presidium members present at the meeting first elected the 
chairman, vice chairmen, and secretary-general of the NPC 
Standing Committee as executive chairmen of the Presidium. 
  The meeting adopted the schedule of the NPC session and the 
namelist of the executive chairman groups. It decided on the 
choice of persons for deputy secretaries-general and on a voting 
method for bills. It also adopted a draft election method for 
the NPC session and a draft decision on approving the request of 
the NPC Standing Committee for accepting the resignation of Yang 
Yanyin from membership of the NPC Standing Committee. The two 
drafts will be printed and transmitted to all delegations for 
deliberation before it is submitted to the plenary session for a 
vote. 
  The meeting set 6:00 PM [1000 GMT] of 16 March as the 
deadline for bill submission by deputies. 
  According to the schedule, the NPC session will last 13 
days. 

</TEXT>

