<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Leader' on Revised Constitution </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0903093094 Beijing XINHUA in English 0854 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0903093094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 9 (XINHUA) -- Deng Xiaoping's theory 
of building socialism with Chinese characteristics will become a 
guiding principle in a revised constitution of the Chinese 
People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), according to 
a top CPPCC leader. 
  Also included in the CPPCC Constitution will be guidelines 
resulting from the recognition that China is at present in the 
primary stage of socialism as well as China's reform goal of 
establishing a socialist market economy, according to Hu Sheng, 
a vice-chairman of the Eighth CPPCC National Committee and one 
of the vice-chairmen of a panel entrusted with revising the 
constitution. 
  New developments in China cry out for a revision of the 
CPPCC 
Constitution, Hu said. In the wake of Deng Xiaoping's 1992 
south China tour and the 14th National Congress of the Chinese 
Communist Party, he said, a new tide of reforms has swept the 
country and the national economy has been surging at an 
unprecedented speed. 
  Furthermore, to conform better to the Constitution of China, 
which was amended last year, a revision of the CPPCC 
Constitution has become more urgent, Hu said. 
  "When all is said, the 1982 CPPCC Constitution is a good 
one," he said. "What we'll do is only a partial revision." 

</TEXT>

