<H3> <TI>   Press Center Receives Correspondents </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0803140794 Beijing XINHUA in English 1342 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0803140794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 8 (XINHUA) -- More than 300 overseas 
reporters attended a reception held here this evening by the 
Press Center for the Second Session of the Eighth National 
People's Congress (NPC) and the Second Session of the Eighth 
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political 
Consultative Conference (CPPCC). 
  By this afternoon, over 1,400 reporters have checked in to 
cover the two events, setting a record. Among them, over 160 
have come from Taiwan, Hong Kong and Macao and more than 200 are 
foreign reporters. 
  The Second Session of the CPPCC Eighth National Committee 
opened here today and the NPC Session is due to open on Thursday 
[10 March]. 
  Zhou Jue, spokesman for NPC, pledged to provide convenient 
conditions for reporters to cover the meetings, including 
interviews with deputies to NPC and members of the CPPCC 
National Committee. 

