<H3> <TI>   `Additional' Rules on Illegal Emigration Promulgated </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0703071394 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0950 
GMT 5 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW0703071394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, 5 Mar (XINHUA) -- The "National People's 
Congress [NPC] Standing Committee Supplementary Regulations on 
Harshly Punishing Crimes of Organizing the Transportation of 
People Across the Territory (Border Areas) Illegally" adopted by 
the NPC Standing Committee at its sixth session on 5 March 1994 
are now promulgated. They become effective upon promulgation. 
  [Signed] Jiang Zemin, PRC President 
  [Dated] 5 March 1994 

</TEXT>

