<F P=100> Central Eurasia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Li Peng Meets Azerbaijani President 8 Mar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0803132794 Beijing XINHUA in English 1303 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0803132794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 8 (XINHUA) -- Chinese Premier Li 
Peng today met with visiting Azerbaijani President Geydar 
Aliyev, urging common efforts to step up bilateral economic 
cooperation and trade. 
  Reviewing the bilateral trade and cooperation, Li Peng said 
that the bilateral trade is still at a comparatively low level 
due to problems in transportation, trade form and areas of 
cooperation. 
  "The two sides should make concerted efforts to expand areas 
of cooperation and promote the development of economic 
cooperation and trade," the Chinese premier said. 
  Aliyev appreciated China's successes in its economic reform 
over the past decade, saying that it is wise to work out 
principles and policies in light of the actual conditions and 
characteristics. 
  Aliyev promised to further its cooperation with China in 
every field. 
  Li Tieying, State Councillor and minister in charge of the 
State Commission for Restructuring the Economy, called at Aliyev 
at the state guesthouse here this afternoon and exchanged views 
with him on economic reforms. 
  Aliyev spoke highly of tremendous achievements China has 
made 
in its reform and opening to the outside world. Azerbaijan is 
ready to study China's successful experience in reform, he said. 

</TEXT>

