<F P=100> West Europe </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sino-Spanish Loan Accord Signed in Madrid </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1003061894 Beijing XINHUA in English 0610 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1003061894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Madrid, March 9 (XINHUA) -- The Bank of China and 
the banking consortium spearheaded by the central American Bank 
of Spain signed here today an agreement of credit loan totalling 
320 million U.S. dollars. 
  The largest-ever credit loan between China and Spain will be 
used by Henan Province to buy Spainish generator sets for its 
"Duck River" power plant project. 
  This accord is believed to play an active role in the 
promotion of the two countries' economic and trade relations. 

</TEXT>

